  <fr:mainmatter>
    <fr:p>a and b are <fr:strong>congruent modulo n</fr:strong>:</fr:p>
    <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a \equiv  b \quad  (mod \ n)]]></fr:tex>
    <fr:p>If <fr:strong>n divides b - a</fr:strong>, or if <fr:strong>b = a + nk</fr:strong> for some integer k This is an <fr:link type="external" href="equivalence%20relation">equivalence relation</fr:link></fr:p>
    <fr:p>So we may consider the <fr:link type="external" href="equivalence%20class">equivalence class</fr:link> -&gt; <fr:link type="local" href="congruence%20class.xml" addr="congruence class" title="Congruence class">congruence class</fr:link> modulo n (<fr:link type="external" href="residue%20class">residue class</fr:link> modulo n)</fr:p>
    <fr:p>
      <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\bar {a} = \{\dots , a-2n, a-n, a, a+n, a+2n, \dots \}]]></fr:tex>
    </fr:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
